Although the 'haunted' feel to this article seems to me like something we'd ordinarily steer clear of as far as SCP ideas, I do really like this article. One thing I did notice in particular was that the [DATA EXPUNGED] sections weren't like running into the reading equivalent of a brick wall, but instead only left out part of an idea while detailing the result a little bit and then maybe leaving out a bit more, and so on. Like so: SCP-382 does [something horrible], feasting on the D's now-mummified corpse, and proceeding to [do something even more horrible]. There's the initial . Which was delightful. I may reference, quote and/or cite this article in future comments regarding issues with [DATA EXPUNGED].







